<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Use a binder for the seeds you’re actively planning and planting, and a box for long-term storage or overflow. This gives you both visibility and protection.
  </p>

  <p>
    Matching the system to how you use your seeds makes everything easier.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Access and storage serve different purposes.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    Binders and boxes are not interchangeable — they solve different problems in seed storage.
  </p>

  <p>
    For most gardeners, using both creates a more effective system than relying on either one alone.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    The right system balances visibility and protection.
  </p>
</section>